1
00:00:51,351 --> 00:00:52,318
Have a good journey!

2
00:01:52,145 --> 00:01:53,169
Open your mouth

3
00:02:14,968 --> 00:02:15,957
What's the matter?

4
00:02:17,537 --> 00:02:18,970
No, no... nothing.

5
00:02:19,305 --> 00:02:20,966
My girlfriend's left me.

6
00:02:55,775 --> 00:02:57,709
Why have you got a white
streak in your hair?

7
00:03:02,348 --> 00:03:03,337
Is something the matter?

8
00:03:03,583 --> 00:03:06,108
Alfred, it's not that
you don't dance well,

9
00:03:06,519 --> 00:03:08,853
but we need a woman in the team,

10
00:03:08,888 --> 00:03:11,457
the rules of the contest say
the team has to be mixed...

11
00:03:11,492 --> 00:03:14,221
with three members...
One of us will have to leave.

12
00:03:14,961 --> 00:03:20,797
I don't feel well... you have
no idea how bad you make me feel.

13
00:03:21,834 --> 00:03:24,234
I've been training for this for months.

14
00:03:25,071 --> 00:03:28,975
It was me who told you of the
contest and registered the team,

15
00:03:29,010 --> 00:03:30,872
and I chose the music
we're going to dance to.

16
00:03:30,907 --> 00:03:32,735
Alfred, don't make things
even more difficult.

17
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:35,474
This isn't happening...

18
00:03:36,549 --> 00:03:37,675
this isn't happening...

19
00:03:39,452 --> 00:03:40,441
this isn't happening.

20
00:03:41,387 --> 00:03:44,982
So why have you got that white streak
if you know people will ask?

21
00:04:09,616 --> 00:04:13,074
PAULA; SORRY. LET'S GET BACK
TOGETHER, NICOLÁS.

22
00:04:16,990 --> 00:04:17,718
Julio.

23
00:04:18,958 --> 00:04:19,890
Nicolás.

24
00:04:23,730 --> 00:04:25,220
Paula's father...

25
00:04:29,569 --> 00:04:32,902
- The shirt I gave you for Christmas.
- Yes.

26
00:04:34,607 --> 00:04:36,837
- It suits you.
- Thank you.

27
00:04:37,910 --> 00:04:39,207
Nice tennis shoes.

28
00:04:41,247 --> 00:04:43,215
Thanks, Paula gave them to me.

29
00:04:44,951 --> 00:04:49,650
Paula's gone to the country.
She needed time.

30
00:04:50,890 --> 00:04:52,949
Where to? What time?

31
00:04:54,894 --> 00:04:59,126
Time. She went to one
of those places to relax...

32
00:04:59,399 --> 00:05:01,629
...where they do yoga...
- Yoga?

33
00:05:02,035 --> 00:05:03,502
When has she ever done yoga?

34
00:05:05,471 --> 00:05:09,407
How's the toy shop?
Are there sales?

35
00:05:10,343 --> 00:05:11,241
Yeah... so so.

36
00:05:17,884 --> 00:05:21,581
- Well, I'm off. Bye.
- Bye.

37
00:05:37,170 --> 00:05:42,107
Hurry up. You still have the quince
and the sweet potato jam to do.

38
00:05:44,077 --> 00:05:45,305
Did you hear?

39
00:05:47,180 --> 00:05:50,316
What's your game, misery!
Do you want to get us both fired?

40
00:05:50,351 --> 00:05:52,917
- I'm not motivated.
- You're not motivated?

41
00:05:52,952 --> 00:05:57,480
You're not Fred Astaire. You're Alfredo
Jiménez... J-i-m-é-n-e-z...

42
00:05:57,790 --> 00:06:01,226
- OK, dad.
- We'll speak about this at home.

43
00:06:15,174 --> 00:06:16,038
Alfred.

44
00:06:16,642 --> 00:06:19,304
Why don't you stop your dad
hitting you in the store?

45
00:06:23,316 --> 00:06:24,783
My dad doesn't hit me.

46
00:06:42,235 --> 00:06:43,702
Can you lend me
your stick deodorant?

47
00:06:45,838 --> 00:06:47,169
Why don't you play football?

48
00:06:47,707 --> 00:06:49,038
Because I had an accident.

49
00:06:50,009 --> 00:06:53,410
- Car accident?
- No, a sports accident.

50
00:06:55,281 --> 00:06:57,977
Your call took me by surprise.
I never thought you'd decide to do it.

51
00:06:59,986 --> 00:07:03,251
The rabbi gave me them
three months ago.

52
00:07:08,361 --> 00:07:09,589
To Miramar, right?

53
00:07:11,998 --> 00:07:14,466
- Don't say a thing.
- I won't say a word.

54
00:07:14,734 --> 00:07:18,363
Our religion forbids cremation.
It's not right.

55
00:07:18,838 --> 00:07:20,066
It's not right.

56
00:07:21,707 --> 00:07:23,766
But I know it's what
your grandfather wanted.

57
00:07:25,178 --> 00:07:28,944
He was a great friend of the rabbi.
I'm a great friend of the rabbi.

58
00:07:29,982 --> 00:07:31,711
I often go to the temple.

59
00:07:33,719 --> 00:07:34,549
Are you sad?

60
00:07:36,889 --> 00:07:37,184
Yes.

61
00:07:38,024 --> 00:07:39,958
You know you're
blocking your emotions.

62
00:07:40,593 --> 00:07:43,528
- Be careful, otherwise you'll explode one day.
- Thanks.

63
00:07:45,131 --> 00:07:47,532
Hello, hello, how are you?

64
00:07:47,567 --> 00:07:51,169
A warm welcome to the Creative Show,
a programme in which

65
00:07:51,204 --> 00:07:57,074
we like to show the most creative
commercials from around the worid.

66
00:07:57,376 --> 00:08:06,614
We also like to analyse the business
so you know the main trends

67
00:08:06,886 --> 00:08:08,786
in advertising in other countries.

68
00:08:08,821 --> 00:08:12,484
Today's programme will be
dedicated to trends.

69
00:08:12,758 --> 00:08:15,927
One trend that we've
detected is balloons.

70
00:08:15,962 --> 00:08:21,834
Suddenly there are balloons
everywhere... for birthday parties...

71
00:08:21,869 --> 00:08:25,497
And there are commercials
such as this one...

72
00:08:28,174 --> 00:08:31,302
Yes? Come in.

73
00:08:48,561 --> 00:08:50,529
Hey, it's the Clio show.

74
00:08:59,939 --> 00:09:02,673
It's incredible Gujis's relevance

75
00:09:02,708 --> 00:09:06,646
Gujis is happy...
and I'll tell you why in a moment.

76
00:09:06,681 --> 00:09:09,444
He's perfect... he was born to it.

77
00:09:18,624 --> 00:09:20,492
Does a juice stain come out with soap?

78
00:09:20,527 --> 00:09:22,361
Use Ariel soap powder. It's very good,

79
00:09:22,396 --> 00:09:23,760
it's sold all over the worid.

80
00:09:25,631 --> 00:09:28,568
But it should come out
with normal soap, right?

81
00:09:28,603 --> 00:09:31,002
Use Ariel, it's good.

82
00:09:31,504 --> 00:09:33,563
- Hi.
- Hi.

83
00:09:34,407 --> 00:09:40,744
- Nicolás, Abril, Abril, Nicolás.
- How are things?

84
00:09:41,047 --> 00:09:44,312
- Fine. You?
- Fine... fine

85
00:09:46,485 --> 00:09:50,251
I'll be right back...
I'm going to change...

86
00:09:51,557 --> 00:09:53,752
Alfred, can you come
here a moment, please?

87
00:09:55,461 --> 00:09:56,655
Who's that girl?

88
00:09:59,966 --> 00:10:01,593
Aren't you going to open the Scalextric?

89
00:10:08,708 --> 00:10:09,732
I don't know.

90
00:10:10,910 --> 00:10:13,012
We look forward to seeing
you all next Saturday

91
00:10:13,047 --> 00:10:14,673
with a new Creative Advertising Show.

92
00:10:17,750 --> 00:10:19,684
We've come to get
you to do something.

93
00:10:21,320 --> 00:10:22,548
I was planning to stay in.

94
00:10:22,955 --> 00:10:27,221
But it's Saturday...
Saturday evening. Everyone goes out.

95
00:10:27,827 --> 00:10:30,625
I always feel as if I'm out of it.

96
00:10:32,098 --> 00:10:35,090
- Out of what?
- Out of everything.

97
00:10:38,838 --> 00:10:40,135
What was your plan?

98
00:10:45,411 --> 00:10:46,935
Why don't you play
with the small bowls?

99
00:10:47,179 --> 00:10:48,748
Don't you see they're
all going down the side?

100
00:10:48,783 --> 00:10:50,773
Let me make my own decisions.

101
00:11:06,399 --> 00:11:08,697
Your shoes are different to mine.

102
00:11:11,337 --> 00:11:12,929
That's because they're mine.

103
00:11:14,674 --> 00:11:15,402
Oh...

104
00:11:16,609 --> 00:11:20,545
- Didn't they give you special shoes?
- No... they said I could use these...

105
00:11:26,452 --> 00:11:28,386
They left me out of the dance team.

106
00:11:30,990 --> 00:11:32,924
It's all very strange.

107
00:11:33,359 --> 00:11:35,293
They said the team had to be mixed.

108
00:11:35,728 --> 00:11:38,993
A woman with a white
streak in her hair appeared.

109
00:11:40,032 --> 00:11:41,329
I still don't get it.

110
00:11:42,334 --> 00:11:43,961
I've got the ashes.

111
00:11:47,339 --> 00:11:48,305
We'll go all the same.

112
00:11:48,340 --> 00:11:51,509
My job is to direct operations
at the toll stations,

113
00:11:51,544 --> 00:11:55,247
and to collect the toll in force both
quickly and efficiently,

114
00:11:55,282 --> 00:11:57,909
interfering as little as
possible with the traffic.

115
00:11:58,150 --> 00:12:01,769
Since the motorway opened
in 1994, the number of drivers

116
00:12:01,804 --> 00:12:05,388
choosing this form of payment
has seen constant growth.

117
00:12:05,691 --> 00:12:08,227
There are currently
over 110,000 clients

118
00:12:08,262 --> 00:12:09,888
and we're still growing.

119
00:12:11,030 --> 00:12:13,225
- You like your job?
- Very much.

120
00:12:13,599 --> 00:12:15,396
Why take the ashes to Miramar?

121
00:12:16,268 --> 00:12:18,600
We used to go there on holiday...
he loved it.

122
00:12:18,871 --> 00:12:21,066
- I don't know it.
- I know.

123
00:12:21,373 --> 00:12:23,637
- Is it big?
- No.

124
00:12:24,076 --> 00:12:25,441
When were you last there?

125
00:12:26,946 --> 00:12:27,810
Twenty years ago.

126
00:12:28,514 --> 00:12:30,482
Like Michael Fox in
'Back to the Future'.

127
00:12:31,350 --> 00:12:33,875
Well, I was hoping to pick up
speed in a straight line.

128
00:12:34,153 --> 00:12:36,087
- In the film, he...
- Yes... yes.

129
00:12:36,122 --> 00:12:38,022
...he goes really fast
as he's being chased,

130
00:12:38,424 --> 00:12:40,984
but then suddenly a car appears...
and guess what he does?

131
00:12:41,293 --> 00:12:42,860
The skateboard
passes under the car

132
00:12:42,895 --> 00:12:45,625
and he goes over the top,
at full speed and

133
00:12:45,898 --> 00:12:49,356
- comes down the front just in time to fall
onto the skate. - Yes.

134
00:12:52,438 --> 00:12:55,464
I did exactly the same thing
but with a park bench.

135
00:12:55,708 --> 00:12:58,075
I tore the ligaments in my knee,

136
00:12:58,110 --> 00:13:00,203
broke my wrist and split
my head open on the ground.

137
00:13:00,713 --> 00:13:04,740
Everybody laughed and
I've never done any sport since.

138
00:13:05,050 --> 00:13:08,178
I was forgetting, Abril's coming with us.
She's visiting her family.

139
00:13:08,587 --> 00:13:09,787
But it was our trip...

140
00:13:09,822 --> 00:13:12,586
It's just three days.
She won't be with us the whole time.

141
00:13:21,033 --> 00:13:22,227
A breadcrumb...

142
00:13:25,104 --> 00:13:26,705
So... we're leaving tomorrow?

143
00:13:26,740 --> 00:13:28,400
- Yes.
- Yes.

144
00:13:30,876 --> 00:13:33,003
- Sleep well.
- You too.

145
00:13:34,380 --> 00:13:35,142
Bye.

146
00:13:36,482 --> 00:13:37,141
Bye.

147
00:13:45,724 --> 00:13:46,520
AWKWARD

148
00:14:45,451 --> 00:14:46,440
Is everything OK?

149
00:14:48,654 --> 00:14:49,382
Fine...

150
00:14:59,899 --> 00:15:01,230
There's Abril.

151
00:15:12,544 --> 00:15:14,205
Help her with her stuff.

152
00:15:24,390 --> 00:15:27,120
- Hello.
- Hello.

153
00:15:29,094 --> 00:15:31,153
- Is something up?
- No, no.

154
00:15:32,197 --> 00:15:34,097
Shall I help you with your things?

155
00:15:48,414 --> 00:15:49,346
Hello.

156
00:16:07,866 --> 00:16:11,199
- You have a Ford.
- Yes.

157
00:16:46,005 --> 00:16:48,200
I couldn't have got lost...

158
00:16:49,408 --> 00:16:53,367
- Do you know why Father Christmas
wears red and white? - No...

159
00:16:54,113 --> 00:16:55,910
Because he was invented by Coca Cola.

160
00:16:56,615 --> 00:16:58,048
He wasn't invented by Coca Cola.

161
00:16:58,817 --> 00:17:02,767
They dressed him like that for an ad...
and that's how he stayed.

162
00:17:02,802 --> 00:17:06,718
- Oh, yeah... so how did he dress before?
- No idea... in blue.

163
00:17:09,695 --> 00:17:12,391
Maybe it was in blue...

164
00:17:13,232 --> 00:17:15,530
Blue and white like
the Argentine flag.

165
00:17:16,168 --> 00:17:18,762
Father Christmas isn't Argentine...
he comes from Alaska.

166
00:17:23,876 --> 00:17:25,909
Have we passed a
sign saying 'Pipinas'?

167
00:17:25,944 --> 00:17:29,175
- This isn't the way to Miramar...
- No, I know it's not.

168
00:17:29,948 --> 00:17:34,019
It's just a little detour
as I need to see Paula.

169
00:17:34,054 --> 00:17:36,385
- Who?
- His ex-girlfriend...

170
00:17:37,656 --> 00:17:42,059
She's not my ex-girlfriend.
We've just cooled things a bit.

171
00:17:43,796 --> 00:17:44,728
Do you love her?

172
00:18:09,288 --> 00:18:11,882
- Let me go with you.
- No, stay here. It'll be OK.

173
00:18:37,249 --> 00:18:38,215
What are you doing here?

174
00:18:38,250 --> 00:18:40,886
What do you mean, what am I doing
here? I've come to get you.

175
00:18:40,921 --> 00:18:44,686
- You're not well, Nicolás.
- Yeah, I'm not well.

176
00:18:45,491 --> 00:18:46,990
I put up a banner in your street;

177
00:18:47,025 --> 00:18:48,754
'Paula, forgive me. Let's get back
together, Nicolás.'

178
00:18:50,129 --> 00:18:52,229
We can't split over a Scalextric.

179
00:18:52,264 --> 00:18:54,049
Nicolás, that was our money
to go to Colonia,

180
00:18:54,084 --> 00:18:55,799
and you spent it on a track
for model cars.

181
00:18:55,834 --> 00:18:58,502
But why go to Colonia?
Every couple goes to Colonia.

182
00:18:58,537 --> 00:19:00,305
What, do we have to go to Colonia
to be considered a real couple?

183
00:19:00,340 --> 00:19:03,475
No, we were never a real couple
because you've got problems.

184
00:19:03,510 --> 00:19:05,177
You need to grow up.
You're very immature.

185
00:19:05,212 --> 00:19:07,577
- Good morning.
- Hello, how are you?

186
00:19:08,080 --> 00:19:10,207
- I haven't opened the Scalextric.
- Go ahead and open it.

187
00:19:10,516 --> 00:19:12,216
- I love you.
- I love you too.

188
00:19:12,251 --> 00:19:14,344
But love is one thing
and being there is another.

189
00:19:15,787 --> 00:19:18,312
It'll be the best thing
for us both, you'll see.

190
00:19:28,901 --> 00:19:31,199
You've still not had
that tooth out, have you?

191
00:19:47,553 --> 00:19:48,986
What are you doing?

192
00:19:49,721 --> 00:19:51,848
Nothing, I'm just giving you courage.

193
00:19:53,592 --> 00:19:56,528
You're working through a failure...
the failure of a relationship.

194
00:19:56,563 --> 00:19:59,563
You need to mourn, everyone
does in their own way.

195
00:19:59,598 --> 00:20:02,362
- I'm thirsty. Is there nothing
to drink? - Me too, very thirsty.

196
00:20:03,135 --> 00:20:04,534
Don't worry, a bit further on...

197
00:20:04,770 --> 00:20:07,830
there's a place where they hand out
mineral water and yogurt.

198
00:20:08,640 --> 00:20:11,200
That's not there any more...
it was years ago.

199
00:20:12,411 --> 00:20:14,709
Anyway, it was in summer, not winter.

200
00:21:24,750 --> 00:21:26,980
- Hello.
- Hello.

201
00:21:28,787 --> 00:21:30,846
- What's wrong?
- With me?

202
00:21:32,491 --> 00:21:37,622
- No, the car. - Uh... well, it suddenly
started making a noise and stopped...

203
00:22:55,440 --> 00:22:56,964
Sorry, are you a nun?

204
00:22:59,745 --> 00:23:00,939
What do you think?

205
00:23:09,121 --> 00:23:12,420
- Where are you going?
- To Miramar.

206
00:23:15,427 --> 00:23:17,588
What are you going
to do there in this cold?

207
00:23:19,931 --> 00:23:21,228
She'going to see her family.

208
00:23:23,702 --> 00:23:27,160
- Is she a writer?
- No, she works in a toll booth.

209
00:23:28,907 --> 00:23:32,934
- What's she jotting down?
- I don't know... I swear I don't.

210
00:23:37,949 --> 00:23:39,211
And the other one?

211
00:23:41,820 --> 00:23:43,186
He's going to a dance contest

212
00:23:43,221 --> 00:23:45,519
but he doesn't know
if he'll be able to dance.

213
00:23:50,228 --> 00:23:51,126
And you?

214
00:23:52,931 --> 00:23:54,865
I'm going to scatter
my grandfather's ashes.

215
00:23:57,903 --> 00:23:59,302
A lovely journey...

216
00:24:06,011 --> 00:24:07,376
- What?
- What?

217
00:24:08,246 --> 00:24:12,410
- You were going to say something.
- No, it was nothing...

218
00:24:16,888 --> 00:24:19,124
- I'd never spoken to a nun before.
- Really?

219
00:24:19,159 --> 00:24:21,820
No, I've never much
to do with religion.

220
00:25:19,784 --> 00:25:22,150
- I'll pay.
- One coffee and seven mineral waters...

221
00:25:22,721 --> 00:25:23,779
- How many?
- Seven.

222
00:25:26,258 --> 00:25:28,317
We can start a kitty later...

223
00:25:34,966 --> 00:25:36,160
Thanks. Shall we go?

224
00:26:24,482 --> 00:26:26,109
Why are you so overdressed?

225
00:26:26,985 --> 00:26:29,286
His father left him in a swimming pool
when he was seven.

226
00:26:29,321 --> 00:26:33,815
He stayed there all night, alone and cold.
It left him traumatised.

227
00:26:34,192 --> 00:26:36,626
So he's always much more warmly
dressed than the others.

228
00:26:36,661 --> 00:26:39,755
Even in summer he doesn't go out very
much because he's embarrassed.

229
00:26:42,667 --> 00:26:43,827
Is that true?

230
00:26:50,008 --> 00:26:53,535
Well... we're here because of a tree.

231
00:26:54,112 --> 00:26:58,014
A tree you reported as stolen, miss.
Is that right?

232
00:27:07,759 --> 00:27:12,958
- What have you got in that urn?
- My grandad's ashes.

233
00:27:16,234 --> 00:27:18,759
- I've got nothing to do with that...
- That's enough.

234
00:27:19,571 --> 00:27:20,936
We've all got our problems.

235
00:27:21,373 --> 00:27:23,534
We don't always know what
others are going through.

236
00:27:24,809 --> 00:27:30,248
Don't worry. Irma, the village
kleptomaniac, has got your tree.

237
00:27:30,283 --> 00:27:32,614
It happens to most tourists.

238
00:27:37,589 --> 00:27:38,715
Bring her in.

239
00:27:43,561 --> 00:27:45,153
What does 'kleptomaniac' mean?

240
00:28:12,223 --> 00:28:16,387
Irma, do me a favour and give
the tree back to this young lady.

241
00:28:20,465 --> 00:28:23,127
Give it back, Irma.
We'll cut you another later.

242
00:28:29,941 --> 00:28:32,876
Come on, woman! Give it back!

243
00:29:15,553 --> 00:29:19,182
So... room 127 for the young lady,

244
00:29:19,624 --> 00:29:23,727
