492
01:01:14,170 --> 01:01:17,970
- Alone?
- Alone.

493
01:01:18,474 --> 01:01:21,272
- Name?
- Alfred...

494
01:01:22,111 --> 01:01:23,305
Surname?

495
01:01:25,481 --> 01:01:29,383
Elliot... Alfred Elliot...

496
01:01:29,719 --> 01:01:32,119
Registration costs fifteen pesos.

497
01:01:38,428 --> 01:01:40,760
How did this competition
get onto Internet?

498
01:01:41,531 --> 01:01:43,556
Everything's on Internet.

499
01:02:14,030 --> 01:02:14,894
How are you?

500
01:02:17,967 --> 01:02:20,231
Well, very well.

501
01:02:21,537 --> 01:02:25,166
- And how are you?
- Fine, fine...

502
01:02:31,280 --> 01:02:33,908
They sang you
Happy Birthday last night...

503
01:02:35,118 --> 01:02:36,107
Ah... yes...

504
01:02:38,454 --> 01:02:41,116
- Did you already know him?
- Who?

505
01:02:41,357 --> 01:02:45,555
- The guy who plays the piano in the
hotel... - No...

506
01:02:47,330 --> 01:02:49,491
And how did he know
it was your birthday?

507
01:02:53,503 --> 01:02:54,731
Don't you think that's weird?

508
01:02:57,306 --> 01:02:59,797
He reminds me of the Wizard of Oz.

509
01:03:00,777 --> 01:03:02,142
What's a pianist doing in that hotel?

510
01:03:02,812 --> 01:03:04,609
The Wizard controls everything...

511
01:03:05,114 --> 01:03:07,275
It's as if he knew things about us.

512
01:03:07,917 --> 01:03:09,407
And in the end he helps them...

513
01:03:10,286 --> 01:03:11,446
I feel he's following me.

514
01:03:12,822 --> 01:03:14,221
How old are you?

515
01:03:20,630 --> 01:03:23,098
Hey, look! Little fish.

516
01:03:28,538 --> 01:03:29,732
Alfred...

517
01:03:37,580 --> 01:03:40,310
- Hello.
- Hello.

518
01:03:43,820 --> 01:03:44,548
Hello.

519
01:03:56,833 --> 01:04:01,969
Hello. I've had this
white streak since I was 12.

520
01:04:02,004 --> 01:04:06,737
- You never let me answer you...
- It looks good on you...

521
01:04:08,811 --> 01:04:15,649
- lf I'd known it meant so much for you...
- Don't worry.

522
01:04:18,621 --> 01:04:19,588
Good luck.

523
01:04:29,732 --> 01:04:31,393
What are you doing out here?

524
01:05:36,432 --> 01:05:40,536
The following contestant is
Alfred Elliot...

525
01:05:40,571 --> 01:05:43,061
from the capital.

526
01:05:53,816 --> 01:05:57,308
- Good evening.
- The microphone's for the presentation...

527
01:06:04,894 --> 01:06:09,297
Well, first of all I'd like to apologise.

528
01:06:11,067 --> 01:06:12,898
I'm here to dance supposedly,

529
01:06:13,402 --> 01:06:15,131
to do something that makes me happy,

530
01:06:15,571 --> 01:06:18,335
that distracts me from
the misery around me.

531
01:06:19,775 --> 01:06:21,344
And I want you to know
I'm not going to do it,

532
01:06:21,379 --> 01:06:22,572
I'm not going to dance.

533
01:06:23,112 --> 01:06:27,378
It's nothing to do with you.
Miramar's lovely... the people too.

534
01:06:28,217 --> 01:06:31,345
Actually, I've not met
many people because...

535
01:06:31,921 --> 01:06:34,991
well, I don't know why but
I've not seen anyone anywhere...

536
01:06:35,026 --> 01:06:36,390
maybe because of the cold,

537
01:06:37,760 --> 01:06:41,423
maybe because everyone's warm at
home and doesn't want to go out.

538
01:06:44,500 --> 01:06:48,904
I've got a real problem with happiness.
Stable people scare me.

539
01:06:48,939 --> 01:06:51,172
I'm not going to get
all sensitive and say;

540
01:06:51,207 --> 01:06:54,343
'the way things are in this
worid you can't be happy.'

541
01:06:54,378 --> 01:06:55,537
No, no, no...

542
01:06:55,878 --> 01:06:58,212
I knew I knew the way things
would be in the worid.

543
01:06:58,247 --> 01:07:02,377
This has only just begun. The way things
are we deserve much more...

544
01:07:03,819 --> 01:07:06,355
I don't want to generalise...
I don't like to generalise...

545
01:07:06,390 --> 01:07:08,687
although I do like surveys.

546
01:07:09,492 --> 01:07:11,756
I'm a caring sort. We have to care.

547
01:07:12,028 --> 01:07:15,431
I walk down the street and
if a guy gives me a flyer I take it.

548
01:07:15,466 --> 01:07:18,232
I realise that the guy
'has' to give out flyers,

549
01:07:18,267 --> 01:07:21,337
I also know he's going to give me
two stuck together instead of one.

550
01:07:21,372 --> 01:07:24,407
But I'll take it and I won't drop
it in the street, no, no, no...

551
01:07:24,442 --> 01:07:29,677
I carry on walking until
I find a bin to throw it in.

552
01:07:29,712 --> 01:07:34,913
And don't tell me I'm immature
and refuse to grow up.

553
01:07:35,251 --> 01:07:38,186
No... why grow up?

554
01:07:39,922 --> 01:07:41,480
Have you seen this?

555
01:07:44,160 --> 01:07:46,060
Have you seen this?

556
01:07:47,763 --> 01:07:50,357
Have you seen this?

557
01:08:46,021 --> 01:08:48,854
I'm dying, I'm dying...

558
01:10:42,004 --> 01:10:43,494
You danced really well last night...

559
01:10:49,278 --> 01:10:52,214
- Were you there?
- Of course I was there.

560
01:10:52,249 --> 01:10:53,909
Did you think I'd miss it?

561
01:10:55,384 --> 01:10:57,978
- I danced well, didn't I?
- Very well.

562
01:11:01,323 --> 01:11:02,950
But it was all for nothing.

563
01:11:04,226 --> 01:11:09,129
Why did they leave?
Why did they leave me alone?

564
01:11:09,498 --> 01:11:12,490
Alfred... Nicolás loves you. Abril too,

565
01:11:12,901 --> 01:11:14,869
but they need each other right now.

566
01:11:15,137 --> 01:11:17,628
But that doesn't mean
you are worth any less.

567
01:11:18,574 --> 01:11:21,668
You were great last night, fabulous.

568
01:11:22,111 --> 01:11:25,547
You've got a marvellous
future ahead of you.

569
01:11:26,148 --> 01:11:31,211
You don't need me or anyone
to tell you what you're worth, see?

570
01:11:36,458 --> 01:11:38,894
Have you tried the cake
they serve at breakfast?

571
01:11:38,929 --> 01:11:41,124
- Delicious.
- Isn't it?

572
01:11:45,000 --> 01:11:49,061
I'm off, Alfred, see you around...

573
01:11:52,174 --> 01:11:53,766
See you...

574
01:12:22,971 --> 01:12:23,960
Is something wrong?

575
01:12:25,641 --> 01:12:26,608
What are we doing here?

576
01:12:29,044 --> 01:12:32,138
I don't know. You were the one who
wanted to come.

577
01:12:40,622 --> 01:12:41,611
What's wrong, Nicolás?

578
01:12:43,158 --> 01:12:44,921
Do we have to stay
here much longer?

579
01:12:45,861 --> 01:12:48,830
No, for just as long as you want.

580
01:13:19,862 --> 01:13:20,829
Here...

581
01:13:31,006 --> 01:13:33,440
I... I brought you to my room because...

582
01:13:34,009 --> 01:13:38,036
so you wouldn't wake
up alone, because...

583
01:13:38,981 --> 01:13:41,472
well... as... as you
weren't feeling too good...

584
01:13:42,618 --> 01:13:46,281
so that... I mean, if you needed
anything... that's why I brought you.

585
01:13:47,856 --> 01:13:50,620
I also brought you your breakfast,
but the thing is that...

586
01:13:51,360 --> 01:13:55,262
...well... there was a chair and I tripped
over it... I dropped the lot...

587
01:13:55,731 --> 01:13:57,494
...I got a bit burnt, nothing serious...

588
01:14:00,235 --> 01:14:03,295
...the croissants are all that's left...

589
01:14:04,006 --> 01:14:06,201
...but you can't eat solids anyway...
so it doesn't matter.

590
01:14:10,179 --> 01:14:14,183
I don't know why I always end up
explaining everything...

591
01:14:14,218 --> 01:14:16,913
like that... too much... I realise...

592
01:14:17,152 --> 01:14:21,452
that I speak about things
of no importance...

593
01:14:23,792 --> 01:14:26,158
well... I do realise...

594
01:14:26,495 --> 01:14:28,326
but it still comes out...

595
01:14:28,997 --> 01:14:33,263
I don't know, at times...
sometimes it seems that...

596
01:14:34,503 --> 01:14:35,993
I speak too much.

597
01:14:38,240 --> 01:14:39,707
I want to leave Miramar.

598
01:14:44,313 --> 01:14:45,371
Me too.

599
01:15:08,804 --> 01:15:09,498
Hello.

600
01:15:10,138 --> 01:15:10,729
Hello.

601
01:15:11,607 --> 01:15:12,266
Hello.

602
01:15:13,242 --> 01:15:17,338
I danced really well last night.
I know you had to leave.

603
01:15:18,213 --> 01:15:19,441
Don't worry.

604
01:15:23,118 --> 01:15:25,916
- Did it hurt?
- What?

605
01:15:26,255 --> 01:15:27,381
Having your tooth out.

606
01:15:29,525 --> 01:15:31,686
Ah... I don't remember.

607
01:15:42,004 --> 01:15:43,699
We're going back, Alfred...

608
01:15:46,942 --> 01:15:48,637
Yes, I know.

609
01:15:50,279 --> 01:15:51,177
That's fine.

610
01:15:52,748 --> 01:15:54,545
Our last breakfast together...

611
01:15:58,453 --> 01:16:01,581
- I'm staying.
- What?

612
01:16:02,357 --> 01:16:03,289
I'm staying.

613
01:16:04,126 --> 01:16:07,490
- Where are you staying?
- Here.

614
01:16:07,525 --> 01:16:10,855
- But you have to go back.
- Why?

615
01:16:11,333 --> 01:16:12,459
What do you mean 'why'?

616
01:16:14,536 --> 01:16:16,231
I have to stay and live here.

617
01:16:18,106 --> 01:16:19,505
The air's different.

618
01:16:21,543 --> 01:16:22,407
Don't worry...

619
01:16:23,745 --> 01:16:25,144
I'll be alright.

620
01:16:50,539 --> 01:16:52,268
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

621
01:17:00,482 --> 01:17:01,915
- Alright?
- Yes.

622
01:17:05,387 --> 01:17:08,447
I think the three of us have something
to say to each other...

623
01:17:11,660 --> 01:17:17,155
I want to say that there
are three people just like us

624
01:17:17,466 --> 01:17:19,195
having breakfast at our table.

625
01:17:25,173 --> 01:17:27,141
That cake...

626
01:17:34,883 --> 01:17:37,252
I want to say thank you
for having come with me...

627
01:17:37,287 --> 01:17:38,719
We've come for each other,

628
01:17:39,154 --> 01:17:40,587
each with the problems of the other...

629
01:17:40,856 --> 01:17:42,619
Yes, well... right... thanks.

630
01:17:43,125 --> 01:17:44,114
I wanted to say,

631
01:17:46,061 --> 01:17:52,364
Nicolás, I love you and
you're a good friend.

632
01:18:01,410 --> 01:18:03,537
OK, shall we go?

633
01:19:14,616 --> 01:19:15,275
What?

634
01:19:19,387 --> 01:19:20,445
What's wrong?

635
01:19:22,791 --> 01:19:23,519
What?

636
01:19:24,593 --> 01:19:25,651
- Nothing...
- What?

637
01:19:26,027 --> 01:19:29,087
- The horoscope...
- The chewing gum horoscope?

638
01:19:31,032 --> 01:19:32,499
What? What does it say?

639
01:19:33,368 --> 01:19:34,858
What does it say?

640
